#### ℹ️ 9. `Func<T, object?>` overload — double `.Select()` boxing

```csharp
// ❌ First Select boxes value types into object, second Select calls .ToString()
collection.Select(objectFormatter).Select(o => o?.ToString())
```

This creates two enumerator allocations and boxes every value-type element. Consider whether this overload is necessary. If it is, collapse into a single Select:

```csharp
return HumanizeDisplayStrings(
    collection.Select(item => objectFormatter(item)?.ToString()),
    separator);
```

